  <datafield tag="520" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">Given a Lie group G , one constructs a principal G -bundle on a manifold X by taking a cover <math altimg="si1.gif" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><mi>U</mi><mo stretchy="false">→</mo><mi>X</mi></math> , specifying a transition cocycle on the cover, and descending the trivialized bundle <math altimg="si2.gif" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><mi>U</mi><mo>×</mo><mi>G</mi></math> along the cover. We demonstrate the existence of an analogous construction for local n -bundles for general n . We establish analogues for simplicial Lie groups of Moore's results on simplicial groups; these imply that bundles for strict Lie n -groups arise from local n -bundles. Our construction leads to simple finite dimensional models of Lie 2-groups such as <math altimg="si3.gif" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">String</mi></mrow><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>n</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo></math> from cocycle data.</subfield>
    <subfield code="9">Elsevier</subfield>
